<TITLE> Annual Ahmadiyya conference begins </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 13 (bdnews24.com)  The Ahmadiyya Muslim Jama'at has started a three-day annual conference, locally known as Jalsha, at its Bakshibazar Office in the city on Friday, says a press release. Representatives from the US, UK, Canada, Pakistan, India and others countries are taking part in the 85th annual conference. Maulana Mohammad Inam Ghori, the representative of Mirza Masroor Ahmad, the spiritual head of the community and incumbent chief of World Ahmadiyya Jama'at , read out the speech of Masroor Ahmad. Peace could be established in the world by mutual sympathy and love through Islam, speakers said at the programme. Representatives of the civil society also spoke in the afternoon
